            <div class="evo-supt4h1-row">
              <div class="evo-supt4h1-row-key">Families</div>
              <div class="evo-supt4h1-row-val">3 unrelated (Israel, Norway, Spain)</div>
            </div>
            <div class="evo-supt4h1-row">
              <div class="evo-supt4h1-row-key">Treatment response</div>
              <div class="evo-supt4h1-row-val"><span class="evo-supt4h1-treatment">Dopamine &rarr; improved motor symptoms</span></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="evo-supt4h1-footer">Source: Canavati et al., <em>Genetics in Medicine</em>, May 2026. EvORanker contributed to the identification; its precise role relative to other methods is not confirmed from accessible text.</div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section" id="limits">
      <h2><span class="num">04 — Honest Limits</span>What the Tool Cannot Do Yet</h2>
      <p>EvORanker's GitHub repository has zero stars and zero forks. No independent researcher has published an assessment of the tool. No external validation study exists. No clinical genomics laboratory has reported integrating EvORanker into its diagnostic workflow. The peer-reviewed results are real, but the tool exists entirely within the orbit of its creators.</p>
      <p>The benchmark gap is significant. EvORanker was tested against ExomeWalker and PHIVE — not against Exomiser, which is the most widely used gene-prioritization tool in clinical genomics and the one a clinician considering adoption would compare it to. Exomiser studies from recent years report diagnostic variants ranked within the top 10 in 85–88% of cases with optimized parameters. Whether EvORanker matches, exceeds, or falls short of that standard is an open question. The 69%/95% figures are strong on their own terms, but "outperformed ExomeWalker and PHIVE" is not the same as "outperformed the current standard of care." The press release language — describing "a new AI breakthrough" — is substantially more expansive than what the published benchmarks support. All secondary media coverage of EvORanker traces to a single Hebrew University press release issued March 29, 2026. No independent journalism exists on this tool.</p>
      <p>Despite these limits, the core results have an unusual property: they are experimentally validated. The DLGAP2 finding was confirmed by a minigene splicing assay. The LPCAT3 finding was corroborated by mouse-model phenotype concordance. The SUPT4H1 finding was replicated across three unrelated families on three continents, with a treatment response. These are not purely computational predictions. They are predictions that survived bench validation. According to the Hebrew University press release, the research team has stated that EvORanker is being applied to cancer research — specifically tumor regression mechanisms — but no paper, data, or named collaborator has been published in connection with that work.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="section" id="signal">
      <h2><span class="num">05 — Signal</span>What Evolution Encodes</h2>
      <p>The deeper claim embedded in EvORanker is not about the tool itself. It is about the data source. Evolution is an experiment in gene function that has been running for approximately four billion years across every branch of the tree of life. Genes that are gained and lost together across 1,028 species share functional constraints — they are part of the same biological systems. This co-occurrence signal exists for every gene in the human genome, including the roughly 15,000 that lack disease annotation in human databases. It is a layer of functional evidence that predates, and is independent of, human medical literature.</p>
      <p>The 13-year arc from Tabach's lab illustrates what it took to make that signal clinically actionable. In 2013, 86 genomes produced co-evolved clusters. In 2021, 1,154 species produced machine-learning predictions with a 14% performance gain. In 2024, 1,028 species and 16 clades produced a clinical gene-ranking tool that identified two disease genes in unsolved pediatric cases. In 2026, the same approach contributed to naming a previously unknown neurodevelopmental disorder — one whose motor symptoms responded to treatment. Each step compressed the distance between evolutionary data and a clinician's decision.</p>
      <p>The LPCAT3 case is the proof of concept. STRING could not detect it. The human disease literature had nothing on it. Only the evolutionary signal — the fact that LPCAT3 co-evolves with genes already linked to intestinal and hepatic function across hundreds of species — identified it as the top candidate. The p-value was 7.93 × 10<sup>−15</sup>. This is not an incremental improvement over existing tools. It is access to evidence those tools cannot see.</p>
      <p>The tool is open-source, written in R, and freely accessible as a Shiny web application. A clinician can enter a gene list and a set of HPO term identifiers and receive a ranked output. What has not changed: no clinical genomics lab has adopted it. The distance between a published paper with strong validation and integration into a diagnostic workflow remains vast. Prof. Yuval Tabach has described thousands of cases worldwide that fall through the cracks of current medicine. The data needed to diagnose some of those children may already exist — encoded not in medical databases, but in the genomes of a thousand species. The bottleneck was never sequencing technology. It was the assumption that you need prior human knowledge to interpret a gene. Evolution has already done the annotation. Someone just had to read it.</p>
    </section>

  </div>
</StoryLayout>

<script>
(function () {
  const canvas = document.querySelector('.evoranker-rare-disease-canvas') as HTMLCanvasElement | null;
  if (!canvas) return;
  const ctx = canvas.getContext('2d');
  if (!ctx) return;

  const EMERALD = '#10b981';
  const EM_R = 16, EM_G = 185, EM_B = 129;
  const GOLD_R = 200, GOLD_G = 150, GOLD_B = 62;
  const BG_COLOR = (getComputedStyle(document.documentElement).getPropertyValue('--bg').trim() || '#f5f0e8');

  const DOT_R = 26, DOT_G = 26, DOT_B = 23;
  const AMB_R = 26, AMB_G = 26, AMB_B = 23;

  let W = 0, H = 0, raf = 0, frame = 0;

  const ro = new ResizeObserver(() => {
    W = canvas.offsetWidth;
    H = canvas.offsetHeight;
    canvas.width = W * devicePixelRatio;
    canvas.height = H * devicePixelRatio;
    ctx.setTransform(devicePixelRatio, 0, 0, devicePixelRatio, 0, 0);
  });
  ro.observe(canvas);

  const prefersReduced = window.matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)').matches;

  const PHASE_STILL = 120;
  const PHASE_WAVES = 540;
  const PHASE_CONVERGE = 720;
  const PHASE_HOLD = 900;
  const PHASE_DISSOLVE = 1080;
  const CYCLE = 1200;

  const NUM_DOTS = 70;
  interface Dot {
    x: number; y: number;
    bx: number; by: number;
    vx: number; vy: number;
    r: number;
    alpha: number;
    baseAlpha: number;
    accum: number;
    flashTimer: number;
  }
  const dots: Dot[] = [];

  const targetIndices: number[] = [];
  let currentTarget = 0;
  let cycleCount = 0;

  function initDots() {
    dots.length = 0;
    const cw = W || 800;
    const ch = H || 380;
    const margin = 40;
    for (let i = 0; i < NUM_DOTS; i++) {
      let dx = 0, dy = 0;
      let attempts = 0;
      do {
        dx = margin + Math.random() * (cw - margin * 2);
        dy = margin + Math.random() * (ch - margin * 2);
        attempts++;
      } while (
        attempts < 20 &&
        Math.abs(dx - cw / 2) < 30 && Math.abs(dy - ch / 2) < 30
      );
      dots.push({
        x: dx, y: dy,
        bx: dx, by: dy,
        vx: (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.1,
        vy: (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.1,
        r: 2.5,
        alpha: 0.12,
        baseAlpha: 0.12,
        accum: 0,
        flashTimer: 0,
      });
    }
    targetIndices.length = 0;
    const scored = dots.map((d, i) => ({
      i,
      dist: Math.sqrt(Math.pow(d.bx - cw / 2, 2) + Math.pow(d.by - ch / 2, 2)),
    }));
    scored.sort((a, b) => a.dist - b.dist);
    const candidates = scored.filter(
      (s) => s.dist > 20 && s.dist < Math.min(cw, ch) * 0.35
    );
    if (candidates.length >= 3) {
      targetIndices.push(candidates[0].i);
      targetIndices.push(candidates[Math.floor(candidates.length / 2)].i);
      targetIndices.push(candidates[candidates.length - 1].i);
    } else {
      targetIndices.push(scored[1].i, scored[3].i, scored[5].i);
    }
  }

  const NUM_AMB = 14;
  interface Amb { x: number; y: number; vx: number; vy: number; r: number; a: number; }
  const ambs: Amb[] = [];

  function initAmb() {
    ambs.length = 0;
    for (let i = 0; i < NUM_AMB; i++) {
      ambs.push({
        x: Math.random() * (W || 800),
        y: Math.random() * (H || 380),
        vx: (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.16,
        vy: (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.16,
        r: 1 + Math.random() * 1.5,
        a: 0.03 + Math.random() * 0.02,
      });
    }
  }

  const NUM_SOURCES = 5;
  interface WaveSource {
    ox: number; oy: number;
    dx: number; dy: number;
    activateAt: number;
    waves: WaveRing[];
    emitTimer: number;
    emitInterval: number;
  }
  interface WaveRing {
    radius: number;
    alpha: number;
    ox: number; oy: number;
    age: number;
    maxAge: number;
  }
  const sources: WaveSource[] = [];
  const edgeConfigs = [
    [
      { ex: 0, ey: 0 },
      { ex: 1, ey: 0.5 },
      { ex: 0.5, ey: 1 },
      { ex: 0.85, ey: 0 },
      { ex: 0, ey: 0.6 },
    ],
    [
      { ex: 0.1, ey: 1 },
      { ex: 0.5, ey: 0 },
      { ex: 1, ey: 0.7 },
      { ex: 0, ey: 0.25 },
      { ex: 0.9, ey: 1 },
    ],
    [
      { ex: 0.4, ey: 0 },
      { ex: 0, ey: 0.5 },
      { ex: 1, ey: 0.9 },
      { ex: 1, ey: 0.2 },
      { ex: 0.2, ey: 1 },
    ],
  ];

  function initSources() {
    sources.length = 0;
    const cw = W || 800;
    const ch = H || 380;
    const cx = cw / 2;
    const cy = ch / 2;
    const configIdx = cycleCount % edgeConfigs.length;
    const config = edgeConfigs[configIdx];

    for (let i = 0; i < NUM_SOURCES; i++) {
      const ox = config[i].ex * cw;
      const oy = config[i].ey * ch;
      const ddx = cx - ox;
      const ddy = cy - oy;
      const dist = Math.sqrt(ddx * ddx + ddy * ddy) || 1;
      sources.push({
        ox, oy,
        dx: ddx / dist,
        dy: ddy / dist,
        activateAt: i * 80,
        waves: [],
        emitTimer: 0,
        emitInterval: 60,
      });
    }
  }

  const pulseRing = { active: false, x: 0, y: 0, radius: 0, alpha: 0 };

  function getPhase(f: number): string {
    const cf = f % CYCLE;
    if (cf < PHASE_STILL) return 'still';
    if (cf < PHASE_WAVES) return 'waves';
    if (cf < PHASE_CONVERGE) return 'converge';
    if (cf < PHASE_HOLD) return 'hold';
    if (cf < PHASE_DISSOLVE) return 'dissolve';
    return 'reset';
  }

  function update() {
    const cf = frame % CYCLE;
    const phase = getPhase(frame);

    if (cf === 0 && frame > 0) {
      cycleCount++;
      currentTarget = cycleCount % targetIndices.length;
      initSources();
      for (const d of dots) {
        d.accum = 0;
        d.alpha = d.baseAlpha;
        d.flashTimer = 0;
      }
      pulseRing.active = false;
    }

    if (frame === 0) initSources();

    const tIdx = targetIndices[currentTarget];

    for (const a of ambs) {
      a.x += a.vx;
      a.y += a.vy;
      if (a.x < -10) a.x = W + 10;
      if (a.x > W + 10) a.x = -10;
      if (a.y < -10) a.y = H + 10;
      if (a.y > H + 10) a.y = -10;
    }

    for (const d of dots) {
      d.vx += (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.02;
      d.vy += (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.02;
      d.vx *= 0.95;
      d.vy *= 0.95;
      d.x = d.bx + d.vx * 5;
      d.y = d.by + d.vy * 5;
    }

    for (const d of dots) {
      if (d.flashTimer > 0) d.flashTimer--;
    }

    if (phase === 'still') {
      for (const d of dots) {
        d.accum = 0;
        d.alpha = d.baseAlpha;
      }
    }

    if (phase === 'waves' || phase === 'converge') {
      const phaseFrame = cf - PHASE_STILL;

      for (const src of sources) {
        if (phaseFrame < src.activateAt) continue;
        const srcAge = phaseFrame - src.activateAt;
        const interval = phase === 'converge' ? 90 : src.emitInterval;

        if (srcAge % interval === 0) {
          let reused = false;
          for (const w of src.waves) {
            if (w.age >= w.maxAge) {
              w.radius = 0;
              w.alpha = 0.10;
              w.ox = src.ox;
              w.oy = src.oy;
              w.age = 0;
              w.maxAge = 200;
              reused = true;
              break;
            }
          }
          if (!reused && src.waves.length < 6) {
            src.waves.push({
              radius: 0,
              alpha: 0.10,
              ox: src.ox,
              oy: src.oy,
              age: 0,
              maxAge: 200,
            });
          }
        }

        for (const w of src.waves) {
          if (w.age >= w.maxAge) continue;
          w.radius += 1.2;
          w.age++;
          w.alpha = Math.max(0.01, 0.10 * (1 - w.age / w.maxAge));

          for (let di = 0; di < dots.length; di++) {
            const d = dots[di];
            const ddx = d.x - w.ox;
            const ddy = d.y - w.oy;
            const dist = Math.sqrt(ddx * ddx + ddy * ddy);
            if (Math.abs(dist - w.radius) < 5 && w.age > 5) {
              if (di === tIdx) {
                d.accum = Math.min(1.0, d.accum + 0.08);
                d.flashTimer = 20;
              } else {
                d.flashTimer = Math.max(d.flashTimer, 15);
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }

      for (let di = 0; di < dots.length; di++) {
        const d = dots[di];
        if (di === tIdx) {
          d.alpha = d.baseAlpha + d.accum * 0.7;
        } else {
          if (d.flashTimer > 0) {
            d.alpha = d.baseAlpha + 0.08 * (d.flashTimer / 15);
          } else {
            d.alpha = d.baseAlpha;
          }
        }
      }
    }

    if (phase === 'converge') {
      const t = (cf - PHASE_WAVES) / (PHASE_CONVERGE - PHASE_WAVES);
      const td = dots[tIdx];
      td.accum = Math.min(1.0, td.accum + 0.02);
      td.r = 2.5 + t * 2.5;
      td.alpha = 0.12 + td.accum * 0.78;

      if (!pulseRing.active && t > 0.4) {
        pulseRing.active = true;
        pulseRing.x = td.x;
        pulseRing.y = td.y;
        pulseRing.radius = 5;
        pulseRing.alpha = 0.2;
      }
    }

    if (phase === 'hold') {
      const t = (cf - PHASE_CONVERGE) / (PHASE_HOLD - PHASE_CONVERGE);
      const td = dots[tIdx];
      td.alpha = 0.9;
      td.r = 5 + Math.sin(t * Math.PI * 4) * 0.5;
      td.accum = 1.0;

      for (const src of sources) {
        src.emitInterval = 120;
        for (const w of src.waves) {
          w.alpha *= 0.98;
        }
      }
    }

    if (phase === 'dissolve') {
      const t = (cf - PHASE_HOLD) / (PHASE_DISSOLVE - PHASE_HOLD);
      const td = dots[tIdx];
      td.r = 5 - t * 2.5;
      td.alpha = 0.9 - t * 0.78;
      td.accum = 1.0 - t;

      for (const src of sources) {
        for (const w of src.waves) {
          w.alpha *= 0.96;
        }
      }

      for (let di = 0; di < dots.length; di++) {
        if (di !== tIdx) {
          dots[di].alpha = dots[di].baseAlpha;
          dots[di].flashTimer = 0;
        }
      }
    }

    if (phase === 'reset') {
      for (const d of dots) {
        d.alpha = d.baseAlpha;
        d.r = 2.5;
        d.accum = 0;
        d.flashTimer = 0;
      }
      for (const src of sources) {
        for (const w of src.waves) {
          w.age = w.maxAge;
        }
      }
      pulseRing.active = false;
    }

    if (pulseRing.active) {
      pulseRing.radius += 0.8;
      pulseRing.alpha = Math.max(0, pulseRing.alpha - 0.0015);
      if (pulseRing.alpha <= 0) pulseRing.active = false;
    }
  }

  function draw() {
    ctx!.fillStyle = BG_COLOR;
    ctx!.fillRect(0, 0, W, H);

    const phase = getPhase(frame);
    const cf = frame % CYCLE;
    const tIdx = targetIndices[currentTarget];

    for (const a of ambs) {
      ctx!.globalAlpha = a.a;
      ctx!.fillStyle = `rgb(${AMB_R},${AMB_G},${AMB_B})`;
      ctx!.beginPath();
      ctx!.arc(a.x, a.y, a.r, 0, Math.PI * 2);
      ctx!.fill();
    }
    ctx!.globalAlpha = 1;

    ctx!.lineWidth = 1;
    for (const src of sources) {
      for (const w of src.waves) {
        if (w.age >= w.maxAge || w.alpha < 0.005) continue;
        ctx!.globalAlpha = w.alpha;
        ctx!.strokeStyle = `rgb(${EM_R},${EM_G},${EM_B})`;
        ctx!.beginPath();
        ctx!.arc(w.ox, w.oy, w.radius, 0, Math.PI * 2);
        ctx!.stroke();
      }
    }
    ctx!.globalAlpha = 1;

    for (let di = 0; di < dots.length; di++) {
      const d = dots[di];
      const isTarget = di === tIdx;
      const isGlowing = isTarget && d.accum > 0.3;

      if (isGlowing) {
        const glowR = 10 + d.accum * 12;
        const grad = ctx!.createRadialGradient(d.x, d.y, 0, d.x, d.y, glowR);
        grad.addColorStop(0, `rgba(${EM_R},${EM_G},${EM_B},${(d.accum * 0.15).toFixed(3)})`);
        grad.addColorStop(1, `rgba(${EM_R},${EM_G},${EM_B},0)`);
        ctx!.fillStyle = grad;
        ctx!.beginPath();
        ctx!.arc(d.x, d.y, glowR, 0, Math.PI * 2);
        ctx!.fill();

        ctx!.globalAlpha = d.alpha;
        ctx!.fillStyle = EMERALD;
        ctx!.beginPath();
        ctx!.arc(d.x, d.y, d.r, 0, Math.PI * 2);
        ctx!.fill();
        ctx!.globalAlpha = 1;
      } else {
        const isFlashing = d.flashTimer > 0;
        ctx!.globalAlpha = d.alpha;
        if (isFlashing) {
          const flashT = d.flashTimer / 15;
          const rr = Math.round(DOT_R + (EM_R - DOT_R) * flashT * 0.3);
          const gg = Math.round(DOT_G + (EM_G - DOT_G) * flashT * 0.3);
          const bb = Math.round(DOT_B + (EM_B - DOT_B) * flashT * 0.3);
          ctx!.fillStyle = `rgb(${rr},${gg},${bb})`;
        } else {
          ctx!.fillStyle = `rgb(${DOT_R},${DOT_G},${DOT_B})`;
        }
        ctx!.beginPath();
        ctx!.arc(d.x, d.y, d.r, 0, Math.PI * 2);
        ctx!.fill();
        ctx!.globalAlpha = 1;
      }
    }

    if (phase === 'hold') {
      const td = dots[tIdx];
      const t = (cf - PHASE_CONVERGE) / (PHASE_HOLD - PHASE_CONVERGE);
      const haloR = 60;
      const haloA = 0.04 * Math.sin(t * Math.PI);
      if (haloA > 0.002) {
        const grad = ctx!.createRadialGradient(td.x, td.y, 0, td.x, td.y, haloR);
        grad.addColorStop(0, `rgba(${GOLD_R},${GOLD_G},${GOLD_B},${haloA.toFixed(3)})`);
        grad.addColorStop(1, `rgba(${GOLD_R},${GOLD_G},${GOLD_B},0)`);
        ctx!.fillStyle = grad;
        ctx!.beginPath();
        ctx!.arc(td.x, td.y, haloR, 0, Math.PI * 2);
        ctx!.fill();
      }
    }

    if (pulseRing.active && pulseRing.alpha > 0.003) {
      ctx!.globalAlpha = pulseRing.alpha;
      ctx!.strokeStyle = `rgb(${EM_R},${EM_G},${EM_B})`;
      ctx!.lineWidth = 1.5;
      ctx!.beginPath();
      ctx!.arc(pulseRing.x, pulseRing.y, pulseRing.radius, 0, Math.PI * 2);
      ctx!.stroke();
      ctx!.globalAlpha = 1;
      ctx!.lineWidth = 1;
    }
  }

  function drawStatic() {
    ctx!.fillStyle = BG_COLOR;
    ctx!.fillRect(0, 0, W, H);

    for (const a of ambs) {
      ctx!.globalAlpha = a.a;
      ctx!.fillStyle = `rgb(${AMB_R},${AMB_G},${AMB_B})`;
      ctx!.beginPath();
      ctx!.arc(a.x, a.y, a.r, 0, Math.PI * 2);
      ctx!.fill();
    }
    ctx!.globalAlpha = 1;

    for (let di = 0; di < dots.length; di++) {
      const d = dots[di];
      const isTarget = di === targetIndices[0];

      if (isTarget) {
        const glowR = 22;
        const grad = ctx!.createRadialGradient(d.x, d.y, 0, d.x, d.y, glowR);
        grad.addColorStop(0, `rgba(${EM_R},${EM_G},${EM_B},0.15)`);
        grad.addColorStop(1, `rgba(${EM_R},${EM_G},${EM_B},0)`);
        ctx!.fillStyle = grad;
        ctx!.beginPath();
        ctx!.arc(d.x, d.y, glowR, 0, Math.PI * 2);
        ctx!.fill();

        ctx!.globalAlpha = 0.9;
        ctx!.fillStyle = EMERALD;
        ctx!.beginPath();
        ctx!.arc(d.x, d.y, 5, 0, Math.PI * 2);
        ctx!.fill();
        ctx!.globalAlpha = 1;

        ctx!.globalAlpha = 0.06;
        ctx!.strokeStyle = `rgb(${EM_R},${EM_G},${EM_B})`;
        ctx!.lineWidth = 1;
        const angles = [0.3, 1.1, 2.4, 3.8, 5.2];
        for (const ang of angles) {
          ctx!.beginPath();
          ctx!.moveTo(d.x + Math.cos(ang) * 30, d.y + Math.sin(ang) * 30);
          ctx!.lineTo(d.x + Math.cos(ang) * 140, d.y + Math.sin(ang) * 140);
          ctx!.stroke();
        }
        ctx!.globalAlpha = 1;
      } else {
        ctx!.globalAlpha = 0.12;
        ctx!.fillStyle = `rgb(${DOT_R},${DOT_G},${DOT_B})`;
        ctx!.beginPath();
        ctx!.arc(d.x, d.y, 2.5, 0, Math.PI * 2);
        ctx!.fill();
        ctx!.globalAlpha = 1;
      }
    }

    const td = dots[targetIndices[0]];
    const grad = ctx!.createRadialGradient(td.x, td.y, 0, td.x, td.y, 60);
    grad.addColorStop(0, `rgba(${GOLD_R},${GOLD_G},${GOLD_B},0.04)`);
    grad.addColorStop(1, `rgba(${GOLD_R},${GOLD_G},${GOLD_B},0)`);
    ctx!.fillStyle = grad;
    ctx!.beginPath();
    ctx!.arc(td.x, td.y, 60, 0, Math.PI * 2);
    ctx!.fill();
  }

  function tick() {
    frame++;
    update();
    draw();
    raf = requestAnimationFrame(tick);
  }

  function init() {
    initDots();
    initAmb();
    initSources();
  }

  requestAnimationFrame(() => {
    init();
    if (prefersReduced) {
      drawStatic();
    } else {
      const io = new IntersectionObserver(([e]) => {
        if (e.isIntersecting) {
          if (!raf) raf = requestAnimationFrame(tick);
        } else {
          cancelAnimationFrame(raf);
          raf = 0;
        }
      }, { threshold: 0.01 });
      io.observe(canvas);

      window.addEventListener('pagehide', () => {
        cancelAnimationFrame(raf);
        io.disconnect();
        ro.disconnect();
      });
    }
  });
})();
</script>
